    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that just using \"national security\" as an excuse to ignore the facts? if a policy is objectively inefficient and drives up costs for regular people, isn't it just bad policy regardless of the political goal? shouldn't economists prioritize the actual economic outcome over these political justifications?",
